messages.msg: Welcome to our site! If you are looking for prayer or someone to chat with, reply to this message or email us at prayer@fightlust.com
Hello
Hello! Welcome to FightLust.com. How can we support you in your journey towards healing today?
Fight against lust

Struggling with lust can be challenging, but we're here to offer guidance and prayer. One powerful prayer you can use is the Deliverance Prayer:

"Heavenly Father, We come before your throne room today through the blood of Jesus Christ. We come boldly and with confidence. (Ephesians 3:12) For your Word says that when we confess our sins, you are faithful and forgive our sins and cleanse us from all unrighteousness. (1 John 1:9) Today, we are praying against the Spirit of lust, lust within our hearts, lust within our minds, lust within our bodies, and the lust of the flesh. The Bible says, the lust of the flesh, the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life (1 John 2:16). So today, we're going to come against that Spirit of lust and all other sexual things that might be connected to it. So today, we're going to pray and renounce these things. Today we renounce all sexual sins that we have been involved in the past, including fornication, masturbation, pornography, perversion, fantasy, and adultery, In the name of Jesus Christ. We break all curses of adultery, perversion, fornication, lust, incest, rape, molestation, harlotry."

You can find more prayers and resources on our site. How else can I assist you today?
I cannot control my mind. Each time i juat have strange sexual thoughts and i cant fight it

I'm sorry to hear that you're struggling, but know that you're not alone. Many people face similar challenges, and there is hope and support available. One key approach is to focus on Christ rather than solely on overcoming the thoughts. Here's a passage that might help:

"Don't focus on freedom from pornography. Focus on Christ; then, you will have freedom from pornography. I guarantee it. Do not pursue freedom. You'll never get it. You may get freedom from pornography, but then you got pride â€“ now you're a slave of pride. You traded one sin for another sin. And freedom doesn't satisfy. When you wake up in the morning, don't think, 'Well, how can I be a self-righteous Pharisee and have freedom today?' Then pat yourself on the back and feel good at the end of the day. No, wake up, and say this: 'I want to behold the beauty of the Lord. My flesh faints for the Living God. I'm thirsting for Him. Earnestly am I going to seek the Lord.' And I'm going to go to bed tonight, I'm going to meditate on the Lord in the watches of the night, and I'm going to see the victories that He gave me throughout the day because I was relying on Him. I don't trust in the arm of my flesh for victory."

Would you like to talk more about this or need specific prayers or resources?
